@startuml state_train_lifecycle

skinparam defaultFontSize 12
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam StateFontSize 13
skinparam StateAttributeFontSize 11

title Train Lifecycle — State Machine (Mandatory + Bonus)

[*] --> Waiting : Train created\n(from input file or GUI)

Waiting --> Running : simTime >= departureTime
Waiting : name, weight, friction
Waiting : accelForce, brakeForce
Waiting : departure → arrival
Waiting : stopDuration

Running --> StoppedAtStation : reached intermediate node
Running --> Delayed : event triggers at node
Running --> Arrived : reached final destination
Running --> Aborted : SimulationStopException\n(GUI stop requested)
Running : physics loop (1s ticks)
Running : accelerate / brake / maintain
Running : speed capped by segment limit
Running : animation callback invoked\n(if --animate or GUI)

StoppedAtStation --> Running : stopTimer reaches 0
StoppedAtStation --> Aborted : SimulationStopException
StoppedAtStation : speed = 0, position = 0
StoppedAtStation : timer counts down from stopDuration

Delayed --> Running : delay timer expires
Delayed --> StoppedAtStation : delay at intermediate node
Delayed --> Aborted : SimulationStopException
Delayed : totalDelay += event.duration
Delayed : clock advances by delay

Arrived --> [*] : .result file finalised
Arrived : actual travel time recorded
Arrived : observer notified

Aborted --> [*] : GUI stop button pressed
Aborted : partial results discarded
Aborted : thrown from usleep / animCallback

note right of Aborted
  **Bonus — GUI Stop**
  SimulationWorker sets
  _stopRequested (atomic).
  Simulation checks flag in
  sleep loop and throws
  SimulationStopException.
end note

note left of Running
  **Bonus — Multi-Run**
  Same lifecycle repeats
  N times with different
  RNG seeds. Statistics
  aggregated afterward.
end note

@enduml
